  "text": "The cohort was derived from the British Columbia Linked Health Dataset [CITATION_1] . This population-based and person-specific database was constructed from records of the provincially administered and largely publicly funded health insurance program. This program covers acute and extended care hospitalization, in-home care, prescription drugs for those over the age of 65 years, diagnostic tests, fees of physicians and, to a limited extent, fees of other health-care practitioners. The linked database covers virtually all residents of British Columbia, each of whom is eligible for insurance coverage. A resident is a person who meets all of the following conditions: must be a citizen of Canada or be lawfully admitted to Canada for permanent residence; must make his or her home in British Columbia; and must be physically present in British Columbia for at least 6 months in a calendar year.",
